com.topcoder.uml.actions.project
Class PrintDiagramAction

java.lang.Object
  com.topcoder.uml.actions.project.PrintDiagramAction
All Implemented Interfaces:
com.topcoder.uml.actionmanager.Action, com.topcoder.uml.actionmanager.TransientAction
public class PrintDiagramAction
extends java.lang.Object
implements com.topcoder.uml.actionmanager.TransientAction

PrintDiagramAction class implements TransientAction interface and it will print diagrams. The diagram should be received as a java.awt.Component, not as a Diagram. The diagram Component should be the graphical representation of the diagram. It will be passed to the Print Manager component.

Thread-safety: This class is immutable, and its thread-safety depends on the Print Manager component.

Version:
1.0
Author:
standlove, TCSDEVELOPER

components

private final java.util.List<java.awt.Component> components

Represents a list java.awt.Component objects to print in the execute method. Initialized when it is declared to an ArrayList object, and its reference is never changed afterwards. It could never be empty.

viewports

private final java.util.List<java.awt.Rectangle> viewports

Represents a list of java.awt.Rectangle objects used as viewports in the execute method. Initialized when it is declared to an ArrayList object, and its reference is never changed afterwards. It could be empty if it is not used, if it is used, it must contain the same number of elements as the components list.

printManager

private final com.topcoder.swing.print.PrintManager printManager

Represents the PrintManager object used to print the diagram in the execute method. Initialized in the constructor and never changed afterwards. It must be non-null.

Method Detail

execute

public void execute()
             throws com.topcoder.uml.actionmanager.ActionExecutionException

Prints the diagram. The diagram should be received as a java.awt.Component, not as a Diagram. The diagram Component should be the graphical representation of the diagram. It will be passed to the Print Manager component.

Impl Note: if the viewports list is non-empty, call printManager#printComponents(components, viewports), otherwise, call printManager#printComponents(components).

Throws:
com.topcoder.uml.actionmanager.ActionExecutionException - if any exception occurs during the execution, it is mainly used to wrap the all possible underlying exceptions.
